laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated with wall thickening and adjacent fat stranding, measuring up to 8 mm. Within the proximal lumen of the appendix is a calcified appendicolith. Other abdominal and pelvic organs appear unremarkable. No fluid collection, no extraluminal gas, and no perforation.
NEGATIVE. FOR QUANTITATION OF POSITIVES, SEND SERUM FOR HCG.
